<li id="cite_note-12"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSalaverriNicolau2015" class="citation book cs1 cs1-prop-long-vol">Salaverri, Joachim; Nicolau, Michaele (2015) [195X]. "Book III – Chapter I – Article III –§1049–50, 1055". <i>Sacrae Theologiae Summa</i>. Vol.&#160;IB: On the Church of Christ, On Holy Scripture. Translated by Baker, Kenneth. Ramsey, New Jersey: Keep the Faith. pp.&#160;423–426. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0991226870" title="Special:BookSources/978-0991226870"><bdi>978-0991226870</bdi></a>. <a href="/wiki/OCLC_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="OCLC (identifier)">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/942788647">942788647</a>. <q><i>In the second part we hold</i>: those persons excommunicated <i>with a total, formal and perfect excommunication</i>, that is, for this purpose legitimately imposed, are also separated from the body of the Church. <br />Therefore  [...] we are not denying that those persons are members of the Church who have been punished only with an excommunication that is material or partial or imperfect.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Book+III+%E2%80%93+Chapter+I+%E2%80%93+Article+III+%E2%80%93%C2%A71049%E2%80%9350%2C+1055&amp;rft.btitle=Sacrae+Theologiae+Summa&amp;rft.place=Ramsey%2C+New+Jersey&amp;rft.pages=423-426&amp;rft.pub=Keep+the+Faith&amp;rft.date=2015&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F942788647&amp;rft.isbn=978-0991226870&amp;rft.aulast=Salaverri&amp;rft.aufirst=Joachim&amp;rft.au=Nicolau%2C+Michaele&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AExcommunication+in+the+Catholic+Church" class="Z3988"></spa